<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="1style.css">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-1BmE4kWBq78iYhFldvKuhfTAU6auU8tT94WrHftjDbrCEXSU1oBoqyl2QvZ6jIW3" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <title>Home | Anime Power Scaling</title>
</head>
<body class="bg-dark text-light">
    <div class="container my-3">
        <nav class="navbar d-flex justify-content-center">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
                <span class="text-light mx-3">-----></span>
                <a href="/" class="mx-3">Home</a>
                <a href="/data" class="mx-3">Databook</a>
                <a href="/rankings" class="mx-3">Rankings</a>
                <a href="/battles" class="mx-3">Battles</a>
                <% if (user) { %>
                <a href="/profile" class="mx-3">Profile</a>
                <% } else { %>
                <a href="/login" class="mx-3">Login/Signup</a>
                <% } %>
                <span class="text-light mx-3"><-----</span>
            </div>
        </nav>

        <main class="text-center my-5 p-5">
            <span>Welcome to...</span>
            <h1 class="text-warning">Anime Power Scaling</h1>
            <p>...where your favorite anime characters go head-to-head to discover who's REALLY the strongest.</p>
            <a href="/signup">Sign up</a><span> to start power scaling now!</span>
        </main>

        <section class="bg-warning text-dark p-5 my-5">
            <h2 class="mb-3 ms-5">What Is Power Scaling?</h2>
            <div class="alignLeft">
                <span>According to </span><a href="https://character-stats-and-profiles.fandom.com/wiki/Powerscaling">this popular wiki</a><span>, powerscaling is defined as "the method of determining a character's power through comparing them to other characters in their series", as well as "attributing feats a character performs to other characters who are equal or greater than that character". APS (Anime Power Scaling) streamlines this process of comparison by allowing users to participate in <a href="/battles">battles</a> between two characters. Additionally, every character has a collection of sources in their <a href="/data">databook</a> for users to reference as evidence to their claims.</span>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="p-5">
            <h2 class="text-end mb-3 me-5">How Do Battles Work?</h2>
            <div class="alignRight">
                <span>Battles are simply two characters whose strengths are being compared by our users. Each user has the opportunity to vote which character they believe would win if they went head-to-head. Each battle works like a forum, where users can comment their reasonings for their vote, and respond to other users who have done the same. After users have voted, the </span><a href="/rankings">global rankings</a><span> will be updated accordingly.</span>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-warning text-dark p-5 my-5">
            <h2 class="mb-3 ms-5">How Do Rankings Work?</h2>
            <div class="alignLeft">
                <span>Rankings are determined by the number of battles each character has won. The more battles a character wins, the higher their global rank will be. Additionally, users can establish their own personal character rankings on their <a href="/profile">profile</a>. We know opinions vary, and not every user has to agree with the current global ranks.</span>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="p-5">
            <h2 class="text-center mb-3">Looking For More?</h2>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
                <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JbgEPqhZo1o">
                    <div class="card m-3 text-center text-dark bg-warning">
                        <img class="cardImg" src="img/psvideo.png" class="card-img-top">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <span>A video explaining powerscaling</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </a>
                <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/PowerScaling/">
                    <div class="card m-3 text-center text-dark bg-warning">
                        <img class="cardImg" src="img/reddit.png" class="card-img-top">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <span>A large powerscaling community</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </a>
                <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fF2-J3mKon8">
                    <div class="card m-3 text-center text-dark bg-warning">
                        <img class="cardImg" src="img/swagkage.png" class="card-img-top">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <span>A very popular powerscaling video</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <nav class="navbar d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
                <span class="text-light mx-3">-----></span>
                <a href="/" class="mx-3">Home</a>
                <a href="/rankings" class="mx-3">Rankings</a>
                <a href="/battles" class="mx-3">Battles</a>
                <% if (user) { %>
                <a href="/Profile" class="mx-3">Profile</a>
                <% } else { %>
                <a href="/login" class="mx-3">Login/Signup</a>
                <% } %>
                <span class="text-light mx-3"><-----</span>
            </div>
        </nav>
    </div>
    <script src="main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>